Title: Fluent Builder Design Pattern in C#
Description:
Follow me on LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/remigiusz-zalewski
Follow me on Medium: https://medium.com/@remigiuszzalewski
Check out my Blog: https://remigiuszzalewski.com

The Fluent builder pattern is a powerful creational design pattern that offers a structured approach to constructing complex objects. It provides a solution to the telescoping constructor problem by encapsulating the logic for object creation in a separate builder class. This pattern is particularly useful when dealing with objects that have numerous optional parameters or when the object construction process involves multiple steps. In C#, the Builder pattern can be implemented with a fluent interface, resulting in a highly expressive and readable API. This approach allows developers to chain method calls, creating a more intuitive and flexible way of constructing objects.

This video tutorial will guide you through the process of implementing the fluent builder pattern in C#. You'll learn how to create a builder class, implement method chaining, and construct complex objects step by step.

Title: Year of embracing curiosity
Description: Resolutions don‚Äôt work. Though it may be limited to my own social bubble, it seems like most people have come to this same conclusion. What does seem to work, though, is themes. You choose a theme and use it as a guiding principle for the countless decisions you‚Äôll face throughout the year.This will be my 4th year of using the theme-based resolution method. I usually take the holiday break to think about what sort of theme would truly make a difference in my life were I to focus on it for a whole year. For the past two weeks, I‚Äôve thought deeply about this and have come up with my theme:Year of embracing curiosityTo those unfamiliar with this method, it may seem oddly vague. The absence of metrics, accountability, or even a clear goal makes it feel like just another sentence. But this is the whole point of a theme: the antithesis of the familiar disappointment that typical resolutions bring ‚Äì a guiding light on the unbeaten path of a new year.So, why this theme? Phrases like ‚ÄúI just don‚Äôt understand,‚Äù ‚Äúthat‚Äôs over my head,‚Äù or ‚ÄúI‚Äôm not smart enough for this‚Äù have always left a bitter taste in my mouth. Yet, I often find myself relying on them. I‚Äôve denied myself knowledge with the underlying notion that my brain wasn‚Äôt wired to understand certain things.Over the last decade, I‚Äôve done away with certain phrases that I didn‚Äôt want to be associated with anymore:- I‚Äôm bored- I‚Äôm lazy- I regret xyzI don‚Äôt say these anymore ‚Äì ever. Phrases like that carve the version of you that exists in your head. This year, I‚Äôll be discontinuing any phrases hinting at an aversion to embracing curiosity. Instead, when I come across something unfamiliar or daunting in complexity, I want to approach it with curiosity. I want to ask more questions about it, do research, and maybe even master a few topics.I‚Äôm starting 2025 by learning Vim ‚Äì an open-source method for editing text and code. It‚Äôs something that I always found intimidating due to its complexity and steep learning curve, but I‚Äôm already 2 weeks in and getting the hang of it. Throughout the year, I plan on tackling other things that I found to be too hard for me to understand or master. Things such as higher-level math, C (programming language), kickboxing, the tax code, and sales.With enough time and effort, anything can be learned.2025 - Year of embracing curiosity2024 - Year of dedicated focus2023 - Year of leap of faith2022 - Year of travel
